 pkg/modules/tracing/listener.go:41: `spanCtx, span := tracing.Start(l.ctx, l.serviceName)`\n\n### Span Attribute Setting\n\n**Prometheus**:\n- storage/remote/queue_manager.go:2299-2311: Sets multiple attributes with `span.SetAttributes()` using type-specific constructors:\n  - `attribute.Int(\"request_size\", sc.reqSize)`\n  - `attribute.String(\"remote_name\", remoteName)`\n- rules/group.go:516: `sp.SetAttributes(attribute.String(\"name\", rule.Name()))`\n- promql/engine.go:1922: `span.SetAttributes(attribute.String(\"operation\", ss.ShortString()))`\n\n**Grafana**:\n- pkg/bus/bus.go:58: `span.SetAttributes(attribute.String(\"msg\", msgName))`\n- pkg/expr/graph.go:128-131: Multiple attributes including `StringSlice` type:\n  - `span.SetAttributes(attribute.String(\"node.refId\", node.RefID()))`\n  - `span.SetAttributes(attribute.StringSlice(\"node.inputRefIDs\", inputRefIDs))`\n- pkg/modules/tracing/listener.go:76-82: Building attributes slice and setting with variadic call\n  - `span.SetAttributes(attributes...)`\n\n### Span Error Recording\n\n**Grafana** demonstrates comprehensive error handling:\n- pkg/modules/tracing/listener.go:92-96: Error pattern in `endSpan()`:\n  ```go\n  if err != nil {\n    l.stateSpan.SetStatus(codes.Error, err.Error())\n    l.stateSpan.RecordError(err)\n  } else {\n    l.stateSpan.SetStatus(codes.Ok, \"\")\n  }\n  ```\n- pkg/tsdb/tempo/metrics_stream.go:81-82: Direct error handling:\n  - `span.RecordError(err)`\n  - `span.SetStatus(codes.Error, err.Error())`\n- pkg/registry/apis/dashboard/datasources.go:50-51: Error attribute and recording:\n  - `span.SetAttributes(attribute.String(\"error\", err.Error()))`\n  - `span.RecordError(err)`\n\n**Prometheus**: No explicit error recording found in the primary span patterns; errors are typically logged separately.\n\n### Additional Options Patterns\n\n- **span.WithSpanKind()**: Both prometheus/prometheus:storage/remote/client.go:402 and scrape/scrape.go:748 use `trace.WithSpanKind(trace.SpanKindClient)` to mark client spans\n- **Span context propagation**: Grafana's listener.go demonstrates nested span context passing and parent-child relationships\n- **Semantic conventions**: prometheus/prometheus references semconv for HTTP attributes (semconv.HTTPResendCount)\n\n### Key Differences\n\n1. **Tracer source**: Prometheus uses global `otel.Tracer(\"\")` while Grafana uses injected `tracer` field or `tracing.Start()` helper\n2. **Error handling**: Grafana explicitly records errors with `RecordError()` and `SetStatus()`, Prometheus does not\n3. **Attribute types**: Both support type-specific attribute constructors; Grafana also uses `StringSlice` for list attributes\n4. **Sampling**: Prometheus uses ratio-based sampling (ParentBased with TraceIDRatioBased), Grafana tests use AlwaysSample\n"
