indClient)` to mark client spans\n- **Span context propagation**: Grafana's listener.go demonstrates nested span context passing and parent-child relationships\n- **Semantic conventions**: prometheus/prometheus references semconv for HTTP attributes (semconv.HTTPResendCount)\n\n### Key Differences\n\n1. **Tracer source**: Prometheus uses global `otel.Tracer(\"\")` while Grafana uses injected `tracer` field or `tracing.Start()` helper\n2. **Error handling**: Grafana explicitly records errors with `RecordError()` and `SetStatus()`, Prometheus does not\n3. **Attribute types**: Both support type-specific attribute constructors; Grafana also uses `StringSlice` for list attributes\n4. **Sampling**: Prometheus uses ratio-based sampling (ParentBased with TraceIDRatioBased), Grafana tests use AlwaysSample\n"
}
